<title>POLAND: Bytom, unions agree on job cut.</title>
<headline>Bytom, unions agree on job cut.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-02-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Polish garment maker Zaklady Odziezowe Bytom SA (Bytom) and trade unions agreed on the need to cut jobs according to the company's restructuring plan, the firm said in a statement on Thursday.</p>
<p>Bytom said it had signed an agreement with all the trade unions at the company, setting down conditions for the layoffs, but gave no details.</p>
<p>Last month Bytom said it would lay off 288 workers on February 28.</p>
